<HEADLINE>
<P>
ONE READER JUST SICK ABOUT LOSING BRICK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am incensed, outraged, curious and baffled at the firing by Channel 13 of 
sports announcer Vic (the Brick) Jacobs. 
</P>
<P>
In a business where bland, run-of-the-mill, cast-from-the-same-mold sports 
announcers abound, Vic is like a breath of fresh air. He may be a brash, 
tell-it-like-it-is ex-New Yorker, but as far as my friends and I are concerned, 
he was the reason we tuned in to the 10 p.m. news. 
</P>
<P>
KIIS is not getting a former TV personality, but rather a sports announcer with 
loads of personality. 
</P>
<P>
JOAN THOMPSON 
</P>
<P>
Sherman Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
