</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREVIOUS NO-HITTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
THIS SEASON: The other 1990 no-hitters were by the Angels' Mark Langston (seven 
innings) and Mike Witt (two) against the Seattle Mariners April 11; by 
Seattle's Randy Johnson against the Detroit Tigers June 2; and Nolan Ryan of 
the Texas Rangers against Oakland June 11. 
</P>
<P>
SAME DAY: On May 2, 1917, at Chicago, Fred Toney of Cincinnati and James 
(Hippo) Vaughn of the Cubs pitched no-hitters in the same day, with Toney and 
the Reds beating Vaughn and the Cubs, 1-0, in 10 innings. 
</P>
<P>
The previous time no-hitters were pitched on the same day in different games 
was April 22, 1898, by Ted Brietenstein of Cincinnati against Pittsburgh, and 
Jim Hughes of Baltimore against the Boston Braves. 
</P>
<P>
SAME MONTH: The last time there were four no-hitters in one month was in May of 
1917, all within five days. On May 2, the Toney-Vaughn double no-hitter was 
pitched. Three days later, Ernie Koob of the St. Louis Browns pitched a 
no-hitter against the Chicago White Sox. The next day Bob Groom, also of the 
Browns, repeated against the White Sox. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
List 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
BASEBALL -- HISTORY; FEATS; SPORTS STATISTICS; 1990 (YEAR) 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
