<P>
Tony Dorsett, the NFL's second-leading career rusher who retired from the 
Denver Broncos last season after injuring his knee in training camp, is 
attempting a comeback, according to The National. The paper reported that 
Dorsett, 36, is working out at the Dallas Cowboys' facilities and has 
instructed his agent to contact other NFL teams. 
</P>
