WEEKEND TV; 
</P>
<P>
ELECTION FEVER STARTS TO BREW BEFORE THE 4TH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE WEINSTEIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two classic movies from 1972, a new cable series and the start of the 1990 
election season light up the small screen this pre-Independence Day weekend. 
</P>
<P>
C-SPAN debuts "Election 90," a weekly program that will focus on the campaigns, 
issues and candidates in this year's gubernatorial and congressional elections, 
Sunday at 6:30 p.m. The first installment examines the Texas governor's race 
between Ann Richards and Clayton Williams. 
</P>
<P>
Tonight at 8, Channel 13 will screen Michael Ritchie's "The Candidate," 
starring Robert Redford as a Kennedy-esque lawyer vying for a California Senate 
seat. Channel 13 also has Bud Cort and Ruth Gordon in the cult classic "Harold 
and Maude," Sunday at 6 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Finally, the one fresh entertainment program on tap this weekend is USA cable 
network's "Counterstrike," premiering Sunday at 10 p.m. The action-adventure 
series stars Christopher Plummer as a crime-fighting mega-mogul. 
</P>
