WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
LIBERIA; 
</P>
<P>
GUERRILLAS BATTLE TROOPS NEAR CAPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rebels battled Liberian troops at four locations in an arc surrounding 
Monrovia, the capital, after capturing the country's main water treatment 
plant. 
</P>
<P>
Civilians who fled the fighting said the guerrillas appeared to be preparing to 
attack the city. The rebels have said they will attack Monrovia unless 
President Samuel K. Doe resigns. They have refused to attend a second round of 
peace talks mediated by the Liberian Council of Churches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
