<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: EX-OFFICER SENTENCED FOR FELONY GRAND THEFT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former Los Angeles police officer was sentenced Friday to three years in 
prison for swindling $50,000 from a wealthy businessman as part of an alleged 
plot to kill two of the man's associates. 
</P>
<P>
Keith Moser, 30, was arrested after accepting $50,000 from businessman Robert 
Furlong as payment in an alleged plot to kill two of Furlong's business 
associates. 
</P>
<P>
Moser, an officer for three years, was acquitted in September of charges of 
solicitation to commit murder, assault and extortion. Jurors deadlocked 8 to 4 
to convict him of the felony grand theft count, and Moser was then retried on 
that charge and convicted May 24. 
</P>
</TEXT>
