<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GARMENT FIRM HEAD GETS RECORD LOCAL INS 
FINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Immigration and Naturalization Service said Friday that it has fined the 
president of a garment manufacturing firm $38,000 for hiring undocumented 
workers. 
</P>
<P>
The amount of the fine against Dae Sug Young of Day Young International Inc. is 
a record in the Los Angeles district, the INS said. 
</P>
<P>
Young was indicted by a federal grand jury in May for making a false statement 
to a government agent. The indictment alleged that Young said he had dismissed 
22 undocumented workers, but a subsequent investigation showed that all 22 were 
still working at the company. 
</P>
<P>
Young faces a federal court hearing on the false statement charge July 31. 
</P>
</TEXT>
