<HEADLINE>
<P>
DESBROW HOLDS ON TO WIN FIRECRACKER 50 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL OLSON, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marty Desbrow of Ventura powered past Jim Jewett of Oxnard on the front 
straightaway of Lap 14 and held on to win the yellow flag-plagued Firecracker 
50 Mini Stock main event at Ventura Raceway on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
Paul Moore of Oxnard finished second in the track's longest race of the season 
and Rock Ake Jr. of Moorpark was third. 
</P>
<P>
Last year's Firecracker 50 champion, Bill Floyd of Ventura, failed to complete 
one lap. 
</P>
<P>
Jim Firsich of Port Hueneme overtook Gary Garvin of Ventura on Lap 5 of the 
15-lap Street Stock main event and held off hard-charging Jim Powell Jr. of 
Cypress for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
It was the fourth main-event win of the season for Firsich. Powell fought his 
way from last place to finish second. Bill Pate of Oxnard was third. 
</P>
<P>
Scott Olsen of Ventura bumped Firsich hard from behind in Turn 1 of the last 
lap to force Firsich high and give Olsen the daylight he needed to win the 
Street Stock six-lap figure-eight main event. Firsich, the Street Stock season 
points leader, held on for second with Ventura's Tom Stephens was third. 
</P>
<P>
Mini Stock figure-eight season points leader Richard Webster of Camarillo led 
wire-to-wire and edged Russ Warren of Van Nuys by one-half car length to win 
the six-lap figure-eight main event. Terry Swauger of Ojai was third. 
</P>
<P>
Mini Stock 10-lap heat winners were Jewett and Kevin Parker of Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
Firsich came from sixth place to win an eight-lap Street Stock heat and Powell 
came from eighth place to win another heat. 
</P>
<P>
Jewett drove to an easy victory in the Mini Stock eight-lap semi-main event. 
Webster was second and Gary Swenson of Ventura third. 
</P>
<P>
Desbrow won the six-lap Mini Stock Trophy Dash and Bill Famularo of Simi Valley 
drove to victory in the four-lap Street Stock Trophy Dash. 
</P>
<P>
Powell set the one-lap fast qualifying time in the Street Stocks at 16.678 
seconds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
